.TH ITS-OTM 1 "June 2026" "ITS-OTM" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
its_otm \- OTM public attestation (Wegman-Carter MAC + SSS chain)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B its_otm
.I COMMAND
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B its_otm
signs payloads with a one-time MAC chain and publishes verification bundles
without revealing the signer state. Verifiers check chain integrity and optional
payload binding.
.PP
PATH may be
.B -
for stdin (read) or stdout (write).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B keygen --out STATE
Create a new signer state file.
.TP
.B sign --state STATE --in PATH --out PATH
Sign a payload; advances the signer chain and updates STATE.
.TP
.B verify --bundle PATH [--payload PATH]
Verify an attestation bundle; optionally check payload matches message field.
.TP
.B demo
Print and self-verify a demo bundle.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR its_asymmetric (1),
.BR its-km (1)
